modules.description: Provides functions to create, resize, and manipulate mutable byte buffers, including reading from and writing to underlying memory. Works with cstructs, a flexible structure for handling binary data with offset and length tracking. Used to efficiently handle network packet buffers and low-level data serialization.

This module offers low-level byte-level operations on mutable buffers, such as parsing, shifting, and converting between binary data and strings, utilizing Cstruct-based bigarrays. It includes endianness-specific numeric handling and delimiter-based subwindow creation, suitable for applications like network protocol parsing and binary file processing.
